WEBVTT

00:05.094 --> 00:06.466
(knocking on door)

00:06.561 --> 00:07.501
JAMIE: <i>Hello, police.</i>

00:07.502 --> 00:09.669
Anybody home?

00:13.208 --> 00:15.374
Hello, police.

00:17.778 --> 00:19.979
Anybody here?

00:24.352 --> 00:26.818
Hello. Hey, police.
Anybody here?

00:29.723 --> 00:31.556
Ma'am, are you okay?

00:31.558 --> 00:32.756
Hey, ma'am. Hello.

00:32.759 --> 00:35.093
Did you inject this?

00:35.095 --> 00:37.695
Any sign of EMS?

00:37.697 --> 00:39.264
JANKO:
They're coming up now.

00:39.266 --> 00:41.099
Hey, back here. Hey, hey.
What do we got?

00:41.101 --> 00:42.466
I don't know. She's not responsive.
Get her off the couch.

00:42.468 --> 00:43.601
Get her down.
Maybe an allergic reaction.

00:43.603 --> 00:45.236
Watch her head.
Ma'am, can you hear us?

00:45.238 --> 00:46.570
Found epinephrine
lying next to her.

00:46.572 --> 00:47.906
Ma'am, can you hear me?
She's in arrest.

00:47.908 --> 00:49.206
Shouldn't it be
making her better?

00:49.208 --> 00:51.008
Sure should be.
Got to get her on the bus.

00:58.683 --> 01:00.250
Get the door.

01:01.287 --> 01:03.253
Hey, need some help out here!

01:03.255 --> 01:04.486
Is she gonna make it?

01:04.489 --> 01:05.622
Doesn't look that way.

01:05.624 --> 01:06.622
What the hell happened?

01:06.624 --> 01:07.790
Welcome to my world.

01:09.000 --> 01:15.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:20.004 --> 01:21.837
Boss, you wanted to see me?

01:21.839 --> 01:22.971
Unfortunately.

01:22.973 --> 01:24.205
Oh.

01:24.207 --> 01:26.541
Matthew Kindler.
Ring a bell?

01:26.543 --> 01:30.979
Yeah, I prosecuted him for a
homicide, maybe a decade ago?

01:30.981 --> 01:33.748
And agreed to some ridiculous
plea deal in the process.

01:33.750 --> 01:35.317
There was nothing
ridiculous about it.

01:35.319 --> 01:37.018
It's 330.20, not responsible

01:37.020 --> 01:39.554
by reason of mental defect
or disease.

01:39.556 --> 01:40.821
He needed a hospital,
not a prison.

01:40.823 --> 01:42.122
Well, soon he may have neither.

01:42.124 --> 01:44.891
He has a retention
hearing next week

01:44.893 --> 01:46.693
to determine if he
should be released.

01:46.695 --> 01:47.894
That's just a formality
in these cases.

01:47.896 --> 01:49.196
Not this time.

01:49.198 --> 01:50.264
What is this?

01:50.266 --> 01:51.298
A confession

01:51.300 --> 01:53.033
for the same murder
you put on Kindler.

01:53.035 --> 01:55.035
That's impossible.

01:55.037 --> 01:57.437
One Pete Cabbad
is claiming responsibility.

01:59.407 --> 02:02.675
You're saying I put an innocent
man away for the past ten years?

02:02.677 --> 02:03.909
He's not innocent.

02:03.911 --> 02:05.631
You of all people
know his criminal history.

02:07.382 --> 02:09.914
The attorney general's office
wants our help

02:09.917 --> 02:11.417
in keeping Kindler
in the hospital.

02:11.419 --> 02:13.353
We're assisting
with the proceedings?

02:13.355 --> 02:15.053
No, you're gonna testify
at the hearing.

02:15.055 --> 02:16.355
Testify?

02:16.357 --> 02:18.190
You're an expert on his history.
The defense will object.

02:18.192 --> 02:20.859
And the judge will overrule.

02:20.861 --> 02:24.596
Erin... with this confession,

02:24.598 --> 02:26.564
the case is on a knife's edge.

02:26.566 --> 02:28.467
And I'm supposed
to tip the scales?

02:28.469 --> 02:31.268
Murder or no murder,
Kindler is dangerous

02:31.270 --> 02:33.471
and he should stay locked up.

02:36.009 --> 02:39.477
Doonan, I'm begging you,
take this office out of it

02:39.479 --> 02:42.246
or else there's gonna be
hell to pay and I mean it.

02:42.248 --> 02:45.082
Take it out.

02:45.084 --> 02:47.351
Right. Got it.

02:47.353 --> 02:50.853
No Can-Doonan strikes again.
Okay. Screw you.

02:50.855 --> 02:52.222
Could you please knock?

02:55.960 --> 02:58.461
There. Mind taking
a look at this?

02:58.463 --> 03:00.063
What is it?
It's a talk I'm taping

03:00.065 --> 03:02.698
for the Major Cities
Chief's Association.

03:02.700 --> 03:03.699
Needs your touch.

03:03.701 --> 03:05.167
You mean it needs
a complete rewrite.

03:05.169 --> 03:06.168
Have at it.

03:06.170 --> 03:08.504
And what's the beef?

03:08.506 --> 03:09.704
Nothing.

03:09.706 --> 03:10.906
Something.

03:10.908 --> 03:13.242
No. Tim Doonan
at the <i>News</i> is running

03:13.244 --> 03:14.876
an investigative
piece tomorrow.

03:14.878 --> 03:16.678
It's a museum-quality frame job.

03:16.680 --> 03:18.213
What's he on me for this time?

03:18.215 --> 03:19.515
Oh, it's not on you. It's on me.

03:19.517 --> 03:22.917
On you? How?

03:22.919 --> 03:25.553
Well, it seems he sourced
every waitress, bartender,

03:25.555 --> 03:28.756
doorman, concierge or owner
that's crossed my path

03:28.758 --> 03:29.957
the last six months of my life.

03:29.959 --> 03:31.159
To what end?

03:31.161 --> 03:33.294
To make it look like I run
with a particular crowd.

03:33.296 --> 03:34.662
Particular how?

03:34.664 --> 03:35.629
Wall Street guys,

03:35.631 --> 03:37.365
sports agents, club owners,

03:37.367 --> 03:39.399
real estate shakers,
you name it.

03:39.401 --> 03:41.668
Never mind me naming it,
what's he naming it?

03:41.670 --> 03:43.570
“The Favor Bank
of Greater New York”

03:43.572 --> 03:45.605
or “The Favor
of the Month Club.”

03:45.607 --> 03:46.639
He hasn't decided the header.

03:46.641 --> 03:49.876
Is it accurate?

03:49.878 --> 03:51.744
Well, there's truth in it,

03:51.746 --> 03:53.780
in that I've been to those
places with those people.

03:53.782 --> 03:55.382
And?

03:55.384 --> 03:57.183
And that's all.

03:57.185 --> 03:58.884
Then there's nothing
to worry about.

03:58.886 --> 04:00.453
Except that
he's also writing that

04:00.455 --> 04:03.456
sometimes the check
doesn't make it to me

04:03.458 --> 04:06.858
or the ticket stub
says “complimentary”.

04:08.729 --> 04:10.796
Did it?

04:10.798 --> 04:13.331
It's not that linear.

04:13.333 --> 04:14.299
Don't spin me, Garrett.

04:14.301 --> 04:15.433
I'm not.
I'm doing my job, Frank.

04:15.435 --> 04:18.168
And what the hell is that
supposed to mean?

04:18.171 --> 04:20.004
Like Sid, like the chiefs
at Intel, Gang Unit,

04:20.005 --> 04:21.839
Counter-Terrorism,
it's part of my job

04:21.841 --> 04:23.141
to keep my ears
to the ground.

04:23.143 --> 04:24.297
It's just different
ground, that's all.

04:24.321 --> 04:24.876
Spin.

04:24.877 --> 04:27.345
To heads-up the alarms...
Spin.

04:27.347 --> 04:29.847
....concerns and event horizons...
And double-talk.

04:29.849 --> 04:32.048
Hold on. Do you demand the other
chiefs give you every detail

04:32.050 --> 04:34.951
about how they bartered every
tidbit and morsel they got?

04:34.953 --> 04:37.454
No, but then I don't
have to read about it

04:37.456 --> 04:39.089
in the paper, either, do I?

04:39.091 --> 04:41.592
No.

04:41.594 --> 04:43.327
It is a talk about ethics
and accountability

04:43.329 --> 04:44.628
in urban policing.

04:44.630 --> 04:47.330
It's going to play at their
convention next weekend.

04:47.332 --> 04:52.502
I'd rather it didn't play to
laughs, so fix your situation.

04:52.504 --> 04:54.703
I can't snap my fingers...
Fix it.

